The Premier League returns this weekend after the international break. Table-toppers Liverpool kick off this round of fixtures, with a home game against Newcastle United. Manchester United will be hoping to pick up only their second win of the season when they welcome Leicester City, while Crystal Palace are away to Tottenham Hotspur. The late kick-off will see Manchester City travel to Norwich. Saturday, September 14
12:30 Liverpool vs Newcastle United
15:00 Brighton & Hove Albion vs Burnley
15:00 Manchester United vs Leicester City
15:00 Sheffield United vs Southampton
15:00 Tottenham Hotspur vs Crystal Palace
15:00 Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Chelsea
